===Interjection===
{{en-interj}}

# {{context|with falling pitch|lang=en}} {{non-gloss definition|used to express [[amusement]] or subtle [[surprise]].}}
#: '''''Huh!''' I'm sure I locked it when I left.''
# {{non-gloss definition|Used to express [[doubt]] or [[confusion]].}}
#: '''''Huh?''' Where did they go?''
# {{context|with rising pitch|lang=en}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to [[reinforce]] a [[question]].}}
#: ''Where were you last night? '''Huh'''?''
# {{rft-sense}} {{context|slang|with falling pitch|lang=en}} {{non-gloss definition|Used either to [[belittle]] the issuer of a statement/question, or [[sarcasm|sarcastically]] to indicate utter agreement, and that the statement being responded to is an extreme [[understatement]]. The intonation is changed to distinguish between the two meanings - implied [[dullness]] for belittlement, and [[feigned]] [[surprise]] for utter agreement.}}
#: ''(belittlement)'' A:"''We should go to an amusement park, it would be fun.''" B:"'''''Huh.'''''"
#: ''(agreement)'' A""''Murder is bad.''" B:"'''''Huh!'''''"
# {{context|informal|with rising pitch|lang=en}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to indicate that one did not hear what was said.}}
#: '''''Huh'''? Could you speak up?''
# {{context|informal|with falling pitch|lang=en}} {{non-gloss definition|Used to create a [[tag question]].}}
#: ''It's getting kind of late, '''huh?'''''

See [[Wikipedia: Speech disfluency#"Huh" {{mdash}} the universal syllable|"Huh" the universal syllable]] Wikipedia

